  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "jv5F3+CJCTNn2A489IZWJ0WpseQ=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "End-to-end sync flow from document edit to cross-device recovery:\n\n```\nUser edits document in Connect\n       \u2193\nReactor stores operation in local PGlite\n       \u2193\nSyncManager detects new ordinal \u2192 populates SwarmChannel outbox\n       \u2193\nSwarmChannel encrypts ops \u2192 uploads to Swarm /bytes \u2192 updates feed pointer\n       \u2193\nOn new device: wallet signature \u2192 same key \u2192 read feeds \u2192 download ops \u2192 replay \u2192 restored\n```\n\nKey properties:\n- Local writes hit PGlite first, so edits never block on network I/O.\n- The outbox is populated reactively by ordinal, not polled.\n- Encryption happens at the SwarmChannel layer before `/bytes` upload.\n- Feed pointers are the only mutable primitive \u2014 the op blobs themselves are immutable.\n- Cross-device recovery is deterministic from the wallet signature alone, no backup seed phrase or extra credentials needed.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
    }
  },
